{{refimprove|date=November 2010}} {{Infobox automobile | image = | name = Jeep FJ | aka = Jeep Fleetvan | manufacturer = {{ubl|[[Willys|Willys Motors]]|[[Kaiser-Jeep]]}} | production = 1961-1975 | assembly = [[Toledo, Ohio]], [[United States]] | predecessor = | class = Compact van | layout = [[FR layout]] | platform = | body_style = | engine = 2.2L ''[[Willys Hurricane engine|F4-134 Hurricane]]'' I4 | transmission = {{ubl|3-speed Borg-Warner ''[[Borg-Warner T-90|T-90]]'' manual|3-speed Borg-Warner ''[[Borg-Warner 35 transmission|35]]'' automatic}} | GVW = {{cvt|4000|lb|kg|0}} | wheelbase = {{ubl|{{convert|81|in|mm|1|abbr=on}} (FJ-3)|{{convert|101|in|mm|1|abbr=on}} (FJ-6)}} | length = {{ubl|{{convert|135|in|mm|1|abbr=on}} (FJ-3)|{{convert|154|in|mm|1|abbr=on}} (FJ-3A, FJ-6)}} | width = {{convert|64.7|in|mm|0|abbr=on}} | height = {{convert|90.1|in|mm|0|abbr=on}} | weight = | related = {{ubl|[[Jeep DJ]]|[[Jeep CJ]]}} | designer = }}
The '''[[Jeep]] FJ Fleetvan''' was a compact delivery van manufactured by [[Willys|Willys Motors]] and [[Kaiser-Jeep]] from 1961 to 1975.<ref Name="Foster">{{cite book |title=The Story of Jeep |last=Foster |first=Patrick R. |authorlink=Patrick R. Foster |year=2004 |publisher=Krause Publications |isbn=0-87349-735-X |page= |pages= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D05p17q4cSYC&dq=%22Jeep+FJ%22&source=gbs_navlinks_s }}</ref> It was based on the [[Jeep DJ|DJ-3A Dispatcher]], but equipped with the [[Willys Hurricane engine|F-134 Hurricane]] engine. Two models were available, the FJ-3 and the longer FJ-3A. It came standard with the familiar Borg-Warner T-90 three-speed manual transmission. A Borg-Warner automatic was offered as an option. Right-hand-drive FJ-3s were made for the U. S. Postal Service. Most of these had horizontal grille slats in contrast to the seven vertical slats found on standard models.
An FJ-6 model (based on the CJ-6) was introduced in 1965 for postal use, which was ultimately replaced by the FJ-8 & FJ-9 introduced in 1975.
